Preconditions:
The input string `n` must not be null.
The input string `n` must not be empty.
The input integer `x` must be a positive integer.

Postconditions:
The returned string must represent the maximum value of `n` after the insertion.
The returned string must have the same length as the input string `n` plus one.
The returned string must have the inserted integer `x` at any position within the string `n`.
The returned string must have the maximum possible value among all possible insertions of `x` into `n`.